This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Computer Architecture) sub-category as it proposes a new computation-centric metric and performance model for datacenter computing. It also touches upon system optimization, which is a key aspect of computer architecture. 

It is also likely to belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category as it focuses on datacenter computing workloads and proposes a new metric and performance model specifically for this domain. 

The paper may also be relevant to the cs.PF (Performance) sub-category as it discusses performance metrics and models. 

The cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category is also a possibility as the proposed metric measures the efficient work defined by the source code, which is a software engineering concern. 

Finally, the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper proposes a new metric and performance model for optimizing system performance.
